\vspace{0.3em}

\subsection{Objectives and Contributions}

The present work makes the following contributions:

\textbf{1. Comprehensive Meta-Analysis.} We synthesize evidence from 405 studies and 983 empirical claims using standardized effect size extraction and coordinate-based activation mapping.

\textbf{2. Three-Tier Theoretical Synthesis.} We organize 48 theoretical models (Core-4) into mechanistic ($\alpha$), integrative ($\beta$), and speculative ($\gamma$) tiers based on evidence strength and replication status. All 9 units together comprise 91 models.

\textbf{3. Cross-Unit Pathway Mapping.} We identify and quantify five high-confidence putative pathways linking spectral, temporal, mnemonic, and affective processing, derived from correlational evidence and requiring future experimental validation.

\textbf{4. \Rthree{} Dimensional Integration.} We map empirical findings onto a unified 10-layer coordinate system spanning acoustic features to semantic representations.

