\section{Results}
\label{sec:results}

\subsection{Study Selection}

The systematic search identified 2,847 potentially relevant records after deduplication. Following title and abstract screening, 612 full-text articles were assessed for eligibility. Of these, 448 studies met inclusion criteria for the full \Cthree{} framework analysis, yielding 1,116 empirical claims and 634 extractable effect sizes across \textbf{all nine cognitive units}.

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=1.15\linewidth]{figures/table1.png}
\vspace{0.3em}
{\fontsize{7}{8.4}\selectfont\textbf{Table 1: Core Unit Evidence Summary with Meta-Analytic Statistics.} Pooled effect sizes across 448 peer-reviewed studies (209 effect sizes).}
\label{tab:core-evidence}
\end{figure}

\textbf{Two-Tier Analytical Strategy.} To balance framework comprehensiveness with methodological rigor, we employed a two-tier approach: (1) \textbf{Full framework synthesis} (all 9 units): Qualitative synthesis, brain region mapping, pathway identification, and theoretical model development included all units regardless of sample size; (2) \textbf{Focused meta-analysis} (Core-4 units only): Quantitative meta-analysis was restricted to units meeting minimum thresholds for reliable pooling ($k \geq 10$ effect sizes after quality filtering). This strategy \textbf{reduces heterogeneity} by focusing on well-studied units with consistent methodologies, while ensuring no important cognitive domain is overlooked in the framework.

