\midrule
L5.pitch\_hz & Pitch frequency & L5 (Perceptual) \\
X18.auditory\_cortex\_activation & Cortical response & X-layer (Neural) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The PSCL model localizes pitch salience computation to anterolateral Heschl's gyrus (alHG), with parametric increases as a function of periodicity strength.

\textbf{Key Evidence (Penagos 2004):}
\begin{center}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}lcc@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Finding} & \textbf{Region} & \textbf{p} \\
\midrule
Pitch salience parametric $\uparrow$ & Anterolateral HG & $<$0.001 \\
Peaked along alHG, not A1 & alHG vs. A1 & $<$0.01 \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\textbf{Falsification Criteria:}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*, topsep=0pt, itemsep=0pt]
\item alHG lesions should abolish pitch salience perception
\item Non-pitched sounds should not activate alHG differentially
\end{itemize}

