\subsubsection{Tier $\alpha$ Models: Auditory-Motor Stream Coupling (AMSC)}

\textbf{\Rthree{} Dimensional Mapping:}
\begin{center}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}lll@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{R³ Dimension} & \textbf{Role} & \textbf{Layer} \\
\midrule
L6.tempo\_bpm & Temporal rate & L6 (Hierarchical) \\
L4.rate\_hz & Rate encoding & L4 (Dimensional) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The AMSC model posits predictive coupling between posterior STG and premotor cortex during rhythmic processing:

\begin{equation}
\text{Motor}_{\text{premotor}}(t) = f(\text{Auditory}_{\text{pSTG}}(t - \Delta))
\label{eq:amsc}
\end{equation}

where $\Delta \approx$ 110 ms represents the predictive lead time.

\textbf{Key Evidence (Potes 2012):}
\begin{center}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}lcc@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Finding} & \textbf{ES} & \textbf{n} \\
\midrule
pSTG high-gamma $\leftrightarrow$ sound intensity & \correlation{0.49} & 8 \\
Auditory $\rightarrow$ motor delay 110 ms & \correlation{0.70} & 4 \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\textbf{Falsification Criteria:}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*, topsep=0pt, itemsep=0pt]
\item Premotor lesions should abolish predictive motor responses
\item Non-rhythmic stimuli should not show auditory-motor coupling
\end{itemize}

