\subsubsection{Tier $\alpha$ Models: Striatal Reward Pathway (SRP)}

The SRP model provides the most mechanistically detailed account of music-induced pleasure, grounded in PET neurochemistry.

\textbf{\Rthree{} Dimensional Mapping:}
\begin{center}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}lll@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{R³ Dimension} & \textbf{Role} & \textbf{Layer} \\
\midrule
L8.valence & Primary output & L8 (Semantic) \\
L8.arousal & Modulating variable & L8 (Semantic) \\
L8.emotion\_category & Categorical output & L8 (Semantic) \\
X14.bold\_signal\_change & Neural correlate & X-layer (Neural) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\textbf{Mathematical Formulation:}
\begin{equation}
P(t) = \beta_1 \cdot \text{DA}_{\text{NAcc}}(t) + \beta_2 \cdot \text{DA}_{\text{Caudate}}(t - \Delta) + \varepsilon
\label{eq:srp}
\end{equation}

where $P(t)$ is subjective pleasure at time $t$, $\text{DA}_{\text{NAcc}}(t)$ is dopamine activity in nucleus accumbens (consummatory), $\text{DA}_{\text{Caudate}}(t-\Delta)$ is dopamine activity in caudate (anticipatory), $\Delta \approx 15$--30s is the temporal offset, $\beta_1 \approx 0.84$ (NAcc contribution), and $\beta_2 \approx 0.71$ (Caudate contribution).

\textbf{Key Evidence:}
\begin{center}
\small
\begin{tabular}{@{}llccc@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Source} & \textbf{Finding} & \textbf{ES} & \textbf{n} & \textbf{p} \\
\midrule
Salimpoor 2011 (PET) & NAcc BP reduction: music $>$ control & \cohend{0.84} & 8 & $<$0.001 \\
Salimpoor 2011 (PET) & NAcc-BP $\leftrightarrow$ pleasure intensity & \correlation{0.84} & 8 & $<$0.01 \\
Salimpoor 2011 (PET) & Caudate-BP $\leftrightarrow$ chills count & \correlation{0.71} & 8 & $<$0.01 \\
Martinez-Molina 2016 & NAcc connectivity in musical anhedonia & \cohend{3.6--7.0} & 45 & $<$0.001 \\
Cheung 2019 & Striatal response to musical surprise & \cohend{3.8--8.5} & 39 & $<$0.001 \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\textbf{Falsification Criteria:}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*, topsep=0pt, itemsep=0pt]
\item Dopamine antagonists should reduce music pleasure (testable via pharmacological manipulation)
\item NAcc lesions should abolish music reward (testable via lesion studies)
\item Musical anhedonics should show selective NAcc disconnection (confirmed: \cohend{-5.89}, Loui 2017)
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Neural Architecture Diagram:}
